\f0\fs24 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Deploy an ADK agent to Agent Runtime using Agents CLI\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 About this codelab\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs24 \cf0 subject
\f0\i0 Last updated Jun 18, 2026\

\f2\i account_circle
\f0\i0 Written by Toni Klopfenstein\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/enterprise-cloud-scale-deploying-the-expense-agent-to-agent-runtime-on-google-cloud#0"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 1. Overview}}
\f1\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 This lab is part of Kaggle's 
\f1\b 5-Day AI Agents: Intensive Vibe Coding Course with Google
\f0\b0 . You can find the additional codelabs and resources available on the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/5-day-ai-agents-intensive-vibecoding-course-with-google"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 event site}}.\
In this codelab, you transition an 
\f1\b ADK 2.0 agent
\f0\b0  from a local development environment into a production-grade deployment. You will use 
\f3\fs26 agents-cli
\f0\fs24  to package, verify, and host your graph-based workflow live on {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://docs.cloud.google.com/gemini-enterprise-agent-platform/build/runtime"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b \cf3 \ul \ulc3 Agent Runtime}} on Google Cloud.\
To explore this deployment process, you will build a local prototype of the 
\f1\b Ambient Expense Agent
\f0\b0  from scratch before deploying it to the cloud. (For a deeper dive into designing this agent's core logic, see the foundational codelabs on the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/5-day-ai-agents-intensive-vibecoding-course-with-google"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 Kaggle event site}}). The Ambient Expense Agent streamlines employee expense reporting by instantly approving standard claims while flagging larger expenses for human-in-the-loop review. Under the hood, it uses an 
\f1\b ADK 2.0 graph-based workflow
\f0\b0  to coordinate these automated approvals and risk analysis steps.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

